MOROCCO – SPAIN BORDER
The Morocco
– Spain border is located along the Plazas de soberanía , Ceuta , Melilla , and Alborán Island along the north coast of Morocco .
Between Morocco and Ceuta is a physical border known as the Ceuta border fence , Melilla also has a physical border known as the Melilla border fence
MARITIME BORDERS Section::::Maritime borders .
Morocco and Spain also share a maritime border in the Canary island area and along the Strait of Gibraltar and the Alboran Sea .
The shortest distance between land along the Strait of Gibraltar is .
The British area of Gibraltar is located on the northern coast of this strait .
